Package: right-click-file
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: zenity, xdg-utils, python3-nautilus
Recommends: nautilus, ding-gnome-shell-extension
Suggests: gnome-shell-extension-manager
Installed-Size: 48
Maintainer: sypher93 <sypher93@proton.me>
Homepage: https://github.com/sypher93/right-click-file
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/sypher93/right-click-file.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/sypher93/right-click-file
Description: Adds "Create a file here..." to the GNOME right-click menu
 Injects a context menu entry into Nautilus and the DING desktop extension
 allowing users to create and immediately open a new file from any folder
 or directly from the desktop.
 .
 Features:
  - Context menu entry in Nautilus file manager
  - Context menu entry on the GNOME desktop (via DING extension)
  - Opens the newly created file automatically in the default text editor
  - Minimal dependencies, no background daemon required
 .
 This package is intended for GNOME desktop environments running Nautilus
 as the default file manager on Debian/Ubuntu-based distributions.